Description

Represents the yt:statistics element used by the YouTube data API

Properties

$_favoriteCount, $_lastWebAccess, $_rootElement, $_rootNamespace, $_subscriberCount, $_videoWatchCount, $_viewCount,

  protected  $_favoriteCount = null

The favoriteCount attribute specifies the number of YouTube users who have added a video to their list of favorite videos. The favoriteCount attribute is only specified when the tag appears within a video entry.integer


  protected  $_lastWebAccess = null

The lastWebAccess attribute indicates the most recent time that a particular user used YouTube.string


  protected  $_rootElement = statistics


  protected  $_rootNamespace = yt


  protected  $_subscriberCount = null

The subscriberCount attribute specifies the number of YouTube users who have subscribed to a particular user's YouTube channel.integer
<p>The subscriberCount attribute is only specified when the <yt:statistics> tag appears within a user profile entry.</p>

  protected  $_videoWatchCount = null

The videoWatchCount attribute specifies the number of videos that a user has watched on YouTube. The videoWatchCount attribute is only specified when the tag appears within a user profile entry.integer


  protected  $_viewCount = null

When the viewCount attribute refers to a video entry, the attribute specifies the number of times that the video has been viewed.integer
<p>When the viewCount attribute refers to a user profile, the attribute specifies the number of times that the user's profile has been viewed.</p>
